Package rs.fon.whibo.problem

Provides interfaces that define the problem and subproblems, used to generate GUI automatically.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Problem
    Every problem should implement this interface and define it's subproblems;
    Subproblem
    Step interface defines methods that describe steps in process.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractComponent
    Base class for all GDT and GC components
    ComponentCompatibilityValidator
    Class which filters available components based on their configuration
    LogGCProgress
    Logger for GC alghoritm and components
    LogGDTProgress
    Logger for GDT alghoritm and components
    LogProgress
    Logger specialized for loging in csv format.
    ProblemBuilder
    This abstract class that creates the specific problem, and defines the subproblems that needs to be solved by components.
    SubproblemData
    This class holds chosen implementation class of components for the subproblem, and their list of Parameters.
    SubproblemParameter
    This class contains parameter min, max, and default values of parameter of the specific component.
    SubproblemParameterReader  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Parameter
    This annotation should be used to annotate parameter field so that property can be read at run time and shown on gui.
